  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nItÂ´s not possible to choose a default wallet. This is bringing some collaterals issue like:\r\nUser can't choose another wallet to register ENS name\r\nUser can't send/receive money with his second wallet\r\n\r\n### Where it Happens\r\nMobile and Desktop\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nJust create an option on the menu to allow user to choose the default wallet or allow him do it by pressing a checkbox near to the wallet's name\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\nSuggestion:\r\n- The first wallet must always be the default wallet\r\n- User must be able to select the default wallet, when he adds another wallet\r\n- User must be able to change the default wallet\r\n- User can't remove the default wallet, except only when this wallet is the only available\r\n- All features related to wallet must point to the default wallet (send,receive, buy cripto, register ens name)\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\n1)Check other wallets as a benchmark.\r\n\r\n2)Gherkin User Story\r\nGiven I want to add more than one wallet,\r\nWhen I add another wallet,\r\nThen a modal should be presented and ask: \"Please choose your default wallet.\"\r\n\r\n3)Question:\r\nIn case of interaction with the chat... Where the wallet attached to the profile is still the first one.\r\na)Will Status allows the user to select a default wallet and use another to chat/other features(third parties) interaction?\r\nFor example: I want to keep anonymous while I'm and I want to receive or spend money(emoticons and other features) with another wallet.\r\n\r\n## Future Steps\r\n\r\n- Create an option to remove wallet.\r\n- Create test cases to validate this default option feature.\r\n- Validate it in mobile and desktop app.\r\n",
